<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@300;400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Your Good Things</h1>
    <ul>
    <% todos.forEach( el => { %>
            <li class='todoItem' data-id='<%=el._id%>'>
                <span class='<%= el.completed === true ? 'completed' : 'not'%>'><%= el.todo %></span>
                <span class='del'> remove </span>
                <span class='count'>day count: <%= el.count %></span>
            </li>
    <% }) %>    
    </ul>

    <h2><%= user.userName %> has <%= left %> things left to do today.</h2>
    <h3>After a few days of success add another small item!</h3>
    <form action="/todos/createTodo" method='POST'>
        <input type="text" placeholder="Add One Good Thing" name='todoItem'>
        <input type="submit">
    </form>

    <a href="/logout" class="logout">Logout</a>

    <p>"So, what if, instead of thinking about solving you whole life, you just think about adding additional good things. One
    at a time. Just let your pile of good things grow.‚Äù - Rainbow Rowell</p>

    <script src="js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>